BEARING WITH WEAKNESSES. 29

And if you do not make yourself all that you wish, How can you bring another to your will?

We would have others saints, And yet we do not root our failings out; We would have others sternly blamed, And yet we love not to be blamed ourselves; Displeased we are when others have free scope to act,

And yet we would not be refused in anything we ask for3 We would have others bound by laws,

And yet in no case can we bear a bond too close.

Thus it is plain how rare it is for us to weigh our neighbours In the same balance with ourselves.

None wise enough.
